-- 04-self-building-test-suite-frames.cell вҖ” full eval-one execution trace
--
-- Ready set analysis:
--   function-spec: all givens have вүЎ (signature, behavior) вҶ’ READY
--   generate-initial-tests: needs function-specвҶ’signature, function-specвҶ’behavior вҶ’ BLOCKED
--   run-tests: needs generate-initial-testsвҶ’test-cases вҶ’ BLOCKED
--   discover-edge-cases: needs run-testsвҶ’results, function-specвҶ’behavior вҶ’ BLOCKED
--   spawn-edge-tests: needs discover-edge-casesвҶ’edge-cases вҶ’ BLOCKED
--   edge-test-*: spawned dynamically вҶ’ BLOCKED (not yet spawned)
--   assess-coverage: needs run-testsвҶ’results, edge-test-*вҶ’result вҶ’ BLOCKED
--   refine-test-suite: needs assess-coverageвҶ’gaps, assess-coverageвҶ’ambiguities вҶ’ BLOCKED
--   final-test-suite: needs all above вҶ’ BLOCKED
--
-- Ready set: { function-spec }
-- Dependency chain: function-spec вҶ’ generate-initial-tests вҶ’ run-tests вҶ’
--   discover-edge-cases вҶ’ [spawn-edge-tests вҶ’ edge-test-*] вҶ’ assess-coverage вҶ’
--   refine-test-suite вҶ’ (вҠўвҲҳ loop) вҶ’ final-test-suite
--
-- The spawner creates a branching point. Before it: linear. After it: fan-out.
-- The вҠўвҲҳ loop wraps discover-edge-cases through refine-test-suite.

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frame 0: function-spec
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

-- function-spec is a data cell вҖ” all yields determined by givens.
-- No вҲҙ body needed. Eval-one freezes immediately.

вҠў function-spec
  given signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  given behavior вүЎ "Parses dates in any common format. Accepts ISO 8601 (2024-03-15, 2024-03-15T10:30:00Z), US format (03/15/2024, March 15 2024), European format (15.03.2024, 15/03/2024), and natural language (next Tuesday, yesterday, in 3 days). Returns a Date with year, month, day fields. Raises ValueError on unparseable input."
  yield signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield behavior вүЎ "Parses dates in any common format. Accepts ISO 8601 (2024-03-15, 2024-03-15T10:30:00Z), US format (03/15/2024, March 15 2024), European format (15.03.2024, 15/03/2024), and natural language (next Tuesday, yesterday, in 3 days). Returns a Date with year, month, day fields. Raises ValueError on unparseable input."

  вҠЁ signature specifies input and output types вҶ’ вң“ (s: string вҶ’ Date)
  вҠЁ behavior describes at least 3 distinct input formats вҶ’ вң“ (ISO, US, European, natural-language)

-- Ready set after frame 0: { generate-initial-tests }

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frame 1: generate-initial-tests
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

-- generate-initial-tests is вҠў (soft). The LLM reads the function spec and
-- produces obvious happy-path test cases, one per format family.

вҠў generate-initial-tests
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  given function-specвҶ’behavior вүЎ "Parses dates in any common format. Accepts ISO 8601 (2024-03-15, 2024-03-15T10:30:00Z), US format (03/15/2024, March 15 2024), European format (15.03.2024, 15/03/2024), and natural language (next Tuesday, yesterday, in 3 days). Returns a Date with year, month, day fields. Raises ValueError on unparseable input."
  yield test-cases[], categories[]

  вҲҙ Given the function В«function-specвҶ’signatureВ» with behavior:
    В«function-specвҶ’behaviorВ»

    Generate 5-7 initial test cases covering the obvious happy paths.
    Each test case is { input, expected-output, category }.
    Categories: "iso", "us", "european", "natural-language", "error".
    Start with the most obvious valid inputs вҖ” one per format family.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- The function accepts 4 format families + error cases.
-- Generate one obvious test per family, plus one error case and one ISO variant.

  yield test-cases вүЎ [
    { input: "2024-03-15", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "iso" },
    { input: "2024-03-15T10:30:00Z", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "iso" },
    { input: "03/15/2024", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "us" },
    { input: "March 15 2024", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "us" },
    { input: "15.03.2024", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "european" },
    { input: "yesterday", expected-output: Date(today.year, today.month, today.day - 1), category: "natural-language" },
    { input: "not-a-date", expected-output: ValueError, category: "error" }
  ]

  yield categories вүЎ ["iso", "us", "european", "natural-language", "error"]

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ length(test-cases) вүҘ 5 вҶ’ вң“ (7 test cases)
--   вҠЁ categories covers at least 3 distinct format families вҶ’ вң“ (5 families)
--   вҠЁ each test-case has input, expected-output, and category fields вҶ’ вң“

-- NOTE: The "yesterday" test has a relative expected-output. This is already
-- hinting at an edge case: relative dates depend on "now". The initial test
-- generator noticed this but didn't flag it вҖ” that's discover-edge-cases' job.

-- Ready set after frame 1: { run-tests }

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frame 2: run-tests
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

-- run-tests is вҠў (soft). Simulates executing parse_date on each test case.

вҠў run-tests
  given generate-initial-testsвҶ’test-cases вүЎ [
    { input: "2024-03-15", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "iso" },
    { input: "2024-03-15T10:30:00Z", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "iso" },
    { input: "03/15/2024", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "us" },
    { input: "March 15 2024", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "us" },
    { input: "15.03.2024", expected-output: Date(2024, 3, 15), category: "european" },
    { input: "yesterday", expected-output: Date(today.year, today.month, today.day - 1), category: "natural-language" },
    { input: "not-a-date", expected-output: ValueError, category: "error" }
  ]
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  given function-specвҶ’behavior вүЎ "Parses dates in any common format..."
  yield results[], pass-count, fail-count

  вҲҙ Simulate executing В«function-specвҶ’signatureВ» on each test case
    in В«generate-initial-testsвҶ’test-casesВ». For each test:
    - Determine what the function SHOULD return given the behavior spec
    - Compare against the test's expected-output
    - Mark as pass or fail with explanation

-- LLM evaluation (simulating parse_date execution):
--
-- Test 1: "2024-03-15" вҶ’ ISO 8601 date. Parse: year=2024, month=3, day=15.
--   Expected: Date(2024, 3, 15). Actual: Date(2024, 3, 15). вҶ’ PASS
--
-- Test 2: "2024-03-15T10:30:00Z" вҶ’ ISO 8601 with time. Date part: 2024-03-15.
--   Expected: Date(2024, 3, 15). Actual: Date(2024, 3, 15). вҶ’ PASS
--   (Time component discarded вҖ” spec says "returns Date with year, month, day")
--
-- Test 3: "03/15/2024" вҶ’ US format MM/DD/YYYY. Month=3, Day=15, Year=2024.
--   Expected: Date(2024, 3, 15). Actual: Date(2024, 3, 15). вҶ’ PASS
--
-- Test 4: "March 15 2024" вҶ’ US written format. Month=March=3, Day=15, Year=2024.
--   Expected: Date(2024, 3, 15). Actual: Date(2024, 3, 15). вҶ’ PASS
--
-- Test 5: "15.03.2024" вҶ’ European DD.MM.YYYY. Day=15, Month=3, Year=2024.
--   Expected: Date(2024, 3, 15). Actual: Date(2024, 3, 15). вҶ’ PASS
--
-- Test 6: "yesterday" вҶ’ Natural language. Relative to today (assume 2024-03-15).
--   Expected: Date(2024, 3, 14). Actual: Date(2024, 3, 14). вҶ’ PASS
--   (But what IS "today"? This test is non-deterministic!)
--
-- Test 7: "not-a-date" вҶ’ Should raise ValueError.
--   Expected: ValueError. Actual: ValueError. вҶ’ PASS

  yield results вүЎ [
    { input: "2024-03-15", actual: Date(2024, 3, 15), expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: "pass", explanation: "Standard ISO 8601 date parsed correctly" },
    { input: "2024-03-15T10:30:00Z", actual: Date(2024, 3, 15), expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: "pass", explanation: "ISO 8601 with time вҖ” date extracted, time discarded per spec" },
    { input: "03/15/2024", actual: Date(2024, 3, 15), expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: "pass", explanation: "US MM/DD/YYYY parsed correctly" },
    { input: "March 15 2024", actual: Date(2024, 3, 15), expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: "pass", explanation: "US written month name parsed correctly" },
    { input: "15.03.2024", actual: Date(2024, 3, 15), expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: "pass", explanation: "European DD.MM.YYYY parsed correctly" },
    { input: "yesterday", actual: Date(2024, 3, 14), expected: Date(2024, 3, 14), verdict: "pass", explanation: "Relative date resolved against assumed 'today'" },
    { input: "not-a-date", actual: ValueError, expected: ValueError, verdict: "pass", explanation: "Unparseable input correctly rejected" }
  ]

  yield pass-count вүЎ 7
  yield fail-count вүЎ 0

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ length(results) = length(test-cases) вҶ’ вң“ (both 7)
--   вҠЁ pass-count + fail-count = length(results) вҶ’ вң“ (7 + 0 = 7)
--   вҠЁ each result includes input, actual, expected, pass/fail, explanation вҶ’ вң“

-- ALL INITIAL TESTS PASS. But this is misleading! We tested only the most
-- obvious inputs. A date parser is a minefield of ambiguity вҖ” edge case
-- discovery is about to reveal how shallow this initial suite really is.

-- Ready set after frame 2: { discover-edge-cases }

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frame 3: discover-edge-cases (вҠўвҲҳ iteration 1)
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

-- discover-edge-cases is вҠў (soft). This is the core insight engine:
-- it reads test results and FINDS GAPS. This cell is the entry point
-- of the вҠўвҲҳ evolution loop.

вҠў discover-edge-cases
  given run-testsвҶ’results вүЎ [
    { input: "2024-03-15", verdict: "pass" },
    { input: "2024-03-15T10:30:00Z", verdict: "pass" },
    { input: "03/15/2024", verdict: "pass" },
    { input: "March 15 2024", verdict: "pass" },
    { input: "15.03.2024", verdict: "pass" },
    { input: "yesterday", verdict: "pass" },
    { input: "not-a-date", verdict: ValueError }
  ]
  given function-specвҶ’behavior вүЎ "Parses dates in any common format..."
  given generate-initial-testsвҶ’categories вүЎ ["iso", "us", "european", "natural-language", "error"]
  yield edge-cases[], reasoning

  вҲҙ Analyze the test results В«run-testsвҶ’resultsВ» and the behavior spec
    В«function-specвҶ’behaviorВ». For each tested category, identify edge cases
    that the initial tests MISSED...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- The initial suite tested 7 happy paths. All passed. But date parsing is
-- NOTORIOUS for edge cases. Let me systematically find what's missing:
--
-- 1. AMBIGUOUS FORMAT: "01/02/2024" вҖ” is this Jan 2 (US) or Feb 1 (European)?
--    The spec lists BOTH US and European formats. Which wins? The function
--    must have a disambiguation strategy, but the spec doesn't say what it is.
--    This is a SPEC BUG, not an implementation bug.
--
-- 2. BOUNDARY: February 29, 2024 вҖ” leap year. Valid. But Feb 29, 2023?
--    Invalid. The parser must know about leap years.
--
-- 3. BOUNDARY: "00/15/2024" вҖ” month 0. "13/15/2024" вҖ” month 13.
--    These are structurally formatted like dates but semantically invalid.
--    Should return ValueError? Or is that only for totally unparseable input?
--
-- 4. PARTIAL: "March 2024" вҖ” no day. What should happen? ValueError?
--    Default to day 1? The spec says "returns Date with year, month, day"
--    but doesn't say all three are required in the input.
--
-- 5. RELATIVE ANCHORING: "next Tuesday" вҖ” from WHEN? The spec says "next
--    Tuesday" is a valid input but doesn't define the reference point.
--    Is it relative to system time? A passed-in reference date? This is
--    another spec ambiguity.
--
-- 6. TWO-DIGIT YEAR: "03/15/24" вҖ” is this 2024 or 1924? Century pivot.
--
-- 7. EMPTY/WHITESPACE: "" and "   " вҖ” should raise ValueError, but
--    some parsers treat these differently from "not-a-date".
--
-- 8. TIMEZONE PRESERVATION: "2024-03-15T10:30:00+05:30" вҖ” non-UTC timezone.
--    Does the date change? 2024-03-15T23:30:00+05:30 is March 16 in UTC.
--    The spec says "returns Date with year, month, day" but doesn't say
--    which timezone the date is in.

  yield edge-cases вүЎ [
    { input: "01/02/2024", risk: "ambiguous-format", description: "US reads Jan 2, European reads Feb 1. Spec supports both formats. Disambiguation strategy unknown.", category: "ambiguous" },
    { input: "2024-02-29", risk: "leap-year-valid", description: "Feb 29 in a leap year. Should parse to Date(2024, 2, 29).", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "2023-02-29", risk: "leap-year-invalid", description: "Feb 29 in a non-leap year. Should raise ValueError вҖ” date doesn't exist.", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "March 2024", risk: "partial-date", description: "No day specified. Spec requires year, month, day in output. Should raise ValueError or default to day 1?", category: "ambiguous" },
    { input: "next Tuesday", risk: "relative-anchor", description: "Relative to what? System clock? No reference date parameter in signature. Non-deterministic.", category: "ambiguous" },
    { input: "03/15/24", risk: "two-digit-year", description: "Is this 2024 or 1924? Century pivot rule unknown.", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "", risk: "empty-input", description: "Empty string. Should raise ValueError. Edge: some parsers return null instead of throwing.", category: "error" },
    { input: "2024-03-15T23:30:00+05:30", risk: "timezone-date-shift", description: "23:30 in +05:30 is March 16 in UTC. Which date does the function return?", category: "ambiguous" }
  ]

  yield reasoning вүЎ "Systematic analysis revealed 8 edge cases across 3 categories: (1) AMBIGUITY вҖ” inputs that are valid in multiple formats with different interpretations (01/02/2024, timezones), (2) BOUNDARIES вҖ” inputs at the edge of validity (leap years, two-digit years), (3) PARTIAL/EMPTY вҖ” inputs that are structurally incomplete. The most critical finding: the spec has at least 3 ambiguities (format disambiguation, relative date anchoring, timezone handling) that make it IMPOSSIBLE to write correct tests without spec clarification. The test suite is building itself by discovering spec bugs."

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ length(edge-cases) вүҘ 4 вҶ’ вң“ (8 edge cases)
--   вҠЁ each edge-case identifies a specific risk or ambiguity вҶ’ вң“
--   вҠЁ edge-cases includes at least one ambiguous input and one boundary case вҶ’ вң“ (4 ambiguous, 2 boundary)
--   вҠЁ reasoning explains the discovery process вҶ’ вң“

-- THE KEY INSIGHT: 7 out of 7 initial tests passed, but the function spec
-- itself has HOLES. The edge case discoverer found the holes not by running
-- more tests but by REASONING about the input space. This is why discover-edge-cases
-- must be soft (вҠў, not вҠў=) вҖ” reasoning about ambiguity requires LLM judgment.

-- Ready set after frame 3: { spawn-edge-tests }

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frame 4: spawn-edge-tests
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

-- spawn-edge-tests is вҠўвҠў (spawner). It creates one edge-test cell per
-- discovered edge case. This is dynamic spawning вҖ” the number of cells
-- created depends on how many edges were found.

вҠўвҠў spawn-edge-tests
  given discover-edge-casesвҶ’edge-cases вүЎ [8 edge cases]
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  given function-specвҶ’behavior вүЎ "Parses dates in any common format..."
  given В§edge-test-template
  yield В§edge-test-cells вүЎ [В§edge-test-1, В§edge-test-2, В§edge-test-3, В§edge-test-4, В§edge-test-5, В§edge-test-6, В§edge-test-7, В§edge-test-8]
  until length(edge-test-cells) = 8

-- 8 cells spawned. They join the frontier. All their givens come from
-- function-spec (already bound) + their specific edge case data (provided
-- by spawner). All 8 are READY simultaneously вҖ” parallelism emerges!
--
-- Ready set after frame 4: { edge-test-1, edge-test-2, ..., edge-test-8 }
-- This is a FAN-OUT: 8 independent cells can execute in any order.

  вҠЁ length(edge-test-cells) = 8 вҶ’ вң“

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frames 5-12: edge-test-1 through edge-test-8 (parallel-eligible)
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

-- All 8 edge test cells are in the ready set. Confluence guarantees
-- execution order doesn't matter. We process them sequentially here
-- but a real runtime could parallelize.

-- --- frame 5: edge-test-1 (ambiguous format) ---

вҠў edge-test-1
  given edge-input вүЎ "01/02/2024"
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Ambiguous: US вҶ’ Date(2024, 1, 2), European вҶ’ Date(2024, 2, 1). Function must choose one or raise ValueError."
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "US reads Jan 2, European reads Feb 1. Spec supports both. No disambiguation rule."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("01/02/2024")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- "01/02/2024" matches both MM/DD/YYYY (US) and DD/MM/YYYY (European).
-- Most date parsers default to locale or try US first. Let's assume US-first.
-- Result: Date(2024, 1, 2) вҖ” but this is a CHOICE, not a fact.
-- The spec doesn't mandate the choice. Verdict: ambiguous.
--
-- Deeper edges from this result:
-- "13/01/2024" вҖ” month 13 in US reading forces European reading. This is
-- IMPLICIT disambiguation: impossible US dates fall back to European.

  yield result вүЎ "Attempted US interpretation: Date(2024, 1, 2). But European interpretation yields Date(2024, 2, 1). Without disambiguation rule, both are valid."
  yield verdict вүЎ "ambiguous"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "13/01/2024", reason: "Month > 12 in US reading forces European fallback вҖ” implicit disambiguation" },
    { input: "01/13/2024", reason: "Day > 12 in European reading forces US fallback вҖ” asymmetric case" }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("ambiguous")
  вҠЁ if verdict = "ambiguous" then result explains the ambiguity вҶ’ вң“

-- --- frame 6: edge-test-2 (leap year valid) ---

вҠў edge-test-2
  given edge-input вүЎ "2024-02-29"
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Should parse to Date(2024, 2, 29). 2024 is a leap year."
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "Boundary: Feb 29 in leap year."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("2024-02-29")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- 2024 is divisible by 4 and not by 100 (or divisible by 400). Leap year. Feb 29 exists.
-- ISO 8601 format. Unambiguous parse.

  yield result вүЎ "Date(2024, 2, 29)"
  yield verdict вүЎ "pass"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "2000-02-29", reason: "Century leap year (divisible by 400) вҖ” common implementation error" },
    { input: "1900-02-29", reason: "Century non-leap year (divisible by 100 but not 400) вҖ” should raise ValueError" }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("pass")

-- --- frame 7: edge-test-3 (leap year invalid) ---

вҠў edge-test-3
  given edge-input вүЎ "2023-02-29"
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Should raise ValueError. 2023 is not a leap year."
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "Boundary: Feb 29 in non-leap year."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("2023-02-29")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- 2023 is not divisible by 4. Not a leap year. Feb 29 doesn't exist.
-- Should raise ValueError вҖ” the date is well-formed but semantically invalid.

  yield result вүЎ "ValueError: February 29 does not exist in 2023"
  yield verdict вүЎ "pass"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "2024-04-31", reason: "April has 30 days вҖ” day overflow in 30-day month" },
    { input: "2024-00-15", reason: "Month 0 вҖ” structural validity vs semantic validity" }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("pass")

-- --- frame 8: edge-test-4 (partial date) ---

вҠў edge-test-4
  given edge-input вүЎ "March 2024"
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Ambiguous: no day. Should raise ValueError or default to day 1. Spec requires year, month, day in output."
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "Partial date вҖ” missing day component."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("March 2024")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- "March 2024" вҖ” recognizable as a month-year pair but no day.
-- The spec says output has year, month, day. Where does day come from?
-- Option A: ValueError (strict вҖ” can't produce complete Date)
-- Option B: Default day to 1 (lenient вҖ” Date(2024, 3, 1))
-- The spec says "Raises ValueError on unparseable input" вҖ” but "March 2024"
-- IS parseable, just incomplete. Ambiguous.

  yield result вүЎ "Spec ambiguity: 'March 2024' is parseable but incomplete. Strict reading вҶ’ ValueError (can't fill day field). Lenient reading вҶ’ Date(2024, 3, 1) (default day=1)."
  yield verdict вүЎ "ambiguous"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "2024", reason: "Even more partial вҖ” just a year. Same ambiguity escalated." },
    { input: "Tuesday", reason: "Day name only, no week/month/year вҖ” maximally partial" }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("ambiguous")
  вҠЁ if verdict = "ambiguous" then result explains the ambiguity вҶ’ вң“

-- --- frame 9: edge-test-5 (relative anchor) ---

вҠў edge-test-5
  given edge-input вүЎ "next Tuesday"
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Ambiguous: relative to what reference date? No reference parameter in signature."
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "Relative date with no anchor point."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("next Tuesday")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- "next Tuesday" requires knowing the current date. The function signature is
-- parse_date(s: string) -> Date вҖ” no reference date parameter. This means
-- the function must use the system clock, making it NON-DETERMINISTIC.
--
-- If today is Wednesday March 13, 2024: next Tuesday = March 19, 2024.
-- If today is Monday March 11, 2024: next Tuesday = March 12, 2024? Or March 19?
-- "Next" Tuesday when today IS Tuesday: is it today or 7 days later?

  yield result вүЎ "Cannot determine without knowing 'today'. Assumes system clock. If today = 2024-03-13 (Wednesday), next Tuesday = 2024-03-19. But: (a) function is non-deterministic, (b) 'next' is ambiguous when today IS Tuesday."
  yield verdict вүЎ "ambiguous"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "last Wednesday", reason: "Same anchoring problem, backwards direction" },
    { input: "in 3 days", reason: "Relative offset вҖ” even more directly clock-dependent" },
    { input: "next Tuesday at 11pm", reason: "Natural language + time вҖ” does time affect which date?" }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("ambiguous")

-- --- frame 10: edge-test-6 (two-digit year) ---

вҠў edge-test-6
  given edge-input вүЎ "03/15/24"
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Two-digit year: 24 вҶ’ 2024 or 1924? Century pivot rule unknown."
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "Year abbreviation вҖ” century assumption required."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("03/15/24")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Two-digit year "24". Common convention: 0-68 вҶ’ 2000s, 69-99 вҶ’ 1900s
-- (POSIX pivot at 2068). So 24 вҶ’ 2024. But this is a convention, not a
-- universal rule. The spec doesn't mention two-digit years at all.
--
-- Also: "03/15/24" could be MM/DD/YY (US) = March 15, 2024
-- or DD/MM/YY (European) = 3rd of month 15 вҶ’ invalid month вҶ’ fallback?

  yield result вүЎ "Assuming POSIX pivot: Date(2024, 3, 15). But: (a) century pivot rule is unspecified, (b) format could be DD/MM/YY if European, yielding month=15 вҶ’ ValueError вҶ’ implicit US fallback."
  yield verdict вүЎ "ambiguous"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "03/15/99", reason: "Year 99 вҖ” is this 1999 or 2099? Pivot boundary." },
    { input: "03/15/00", reason: "Year 00 вҖ” is this 2000 or 1900? Y2K edge." }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("ambiguous")

-- --- frame 11: edge-test-7 (empty input) ---

вҠў edge-test-7
  given edge-input вүЎ ""
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Should raise ValueError. Empty string is unparseable."
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "Empty input вҖ” degenerate case."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Empty string. Nothing to parse. ValueError per spec.

  yield result вүЎ "ValueError: empty string"
  yield verdict вүЎ "pass"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "   ", reason: "Whitespace-only вҖ” trimmed to empty? Or separate error?" },
    { input: "\t\n", reason: "Non-space whitespace вҖ” tab and newline" }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("pass")

-- --- frame 12: edge-test-8 (timezone date shift) ---

вҠў edge-test-8
  given edge-input вүЎ "2024-03-15T23:30:00+05:30"
  given expected-behavior вүЎ "Ambiguous: 23:30 in +05:30 is 18:00 UTC (same day) BUT if offset were larger, date could shift. Which timezone determines the date?"
  given edge-rationale вүЎ "Timezone offset that could shift the calendar date."
  given function-specвҶ’signature вүЎ "parse_date(s: string) -> Date"
  yield result, verdict, deeper-edges[]

  вҲҙ Simulate executing parse_date("2024-03-15T23:30:00+05:30")...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- "2024-03-15T23:30:00+05:30" вҖ” March 15 at 23:30 in IST (+05:30).
-- In UTC this is 18:00 on March 15. Same calendar date. So Date(2024, 3, 15).
-- BUT: "2024-03-15T02:00:00+05:30" вҶ’ UTC 20:30 on March 14. Date SHIFTS!
-- The spec doesn't say whether to use local date or UTC date.

  yield result вүЎ "Date(2024, 3, 15) if using local timezone, same in UTC. But edge: '2024-03-15T02:00:00+05:30' вҶ’ UTC March 14. Spec doesn't specify UTC vs local."
  yield verdict вүЎ "ambiguous"
  yield deeper-edges вүЎ [
    { input: "2024-03-15T02:00:00+05:30", reason: "Local is March 15, UTC is March 14 вҖ” date ACTUALLY shifts" },
    { input: "2024-03-15T00:30:00-11:00", reason: "Extreme negative offset вҖ” local is March 15, UTC is March 15 11:30 вҖ” no shift, but close" }
  ]

  вҠЁ verdict вҲҲ { "pass", "fail", "ambiguous" } вҶ’ вң“ ("ambiguous")

-- All 8 edge tests complete. Key finding: 5 out of 8 are AMBIGUOUS.
-- The test suite isn't just finding bugs вҖ” it's finding SPEC GAPS.
-- This is the self-building insight: tests reveal spec deficiencies.

