вҠў refine-test-suite
  given assess-coverageвҶ’gaps вүЎ [7 gaps]
  given assess-coverageвҶ’ambiguities вүЎ [5 ambiguities]
  given discover-edge-casesвҶ’edge-cases вүЎ [8 original edge cases]
  yield refined-edge-cases[], spec-clarifications[]

  вҲҙ Given remaining gaps and ambiguities, produce new edge cases and spec questions...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Map each gap to a targeted edge case. For ambiguities, produce spec questions.

  yield refined-edge-cases вүЎ [
    { input: "2000-02-29", risk: "century-leap", description: "Year 2000 is a leap year (divisible by 400). Must parse to Date(2000, 2, 29).", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "1900-02-29", risk: "century-non-leap", description: "Year 1900 is NOT a leap year (divisible by 100, not 400). Must raise ValueError.", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "2024-04-31", risk: "day-overflow-30", description: "April has 30 days. Apr 31 doesn't exist. Must raise ValueError.", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "2024-00-15", risk: "month-zero", description: "Month 0 is invalid. Must raise ValueError.", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "   ", risk: "whitespace-only", description: "Whitespace-only string. Should raise ValueError after trimming.", category: "error" },
    { input: "13/01/2024", risk: "implicit-disambiguation", description: "Month > 12 in US reading. Forces European interpretation: Jan 13, 2024.", category: "boundary" },
    { input: "last Wednesday", risk: "reverse-relative", description: "Relative date in past direction. Same anchoring problem as 'next Tuesday'.", category: "natural-language" }
  ]

  yield spec-clarifications вүЎ [
    "Q1: When input matches both US (MM/DD) and European (DD/MM) formats, which takes precedence? Or should the function raise an error for ambiguous inputs?",
    "Q2: Should partial dates ('March 2024', '2024', 'Tuesday') raise ValueError, or should missing fields have defaults (dayвҶ’1, monthвҶ’1, yearвҶ’current)?",
    "Q3: For relative dates ('next Tuesday', 'yesterday'), what is the reference point? System clock? Or should the function accept an optional reference date parameter?",
    "Q4: For two-digit years, what century pivot should be used? POSIX (69/2069, 70/1970)? Or always assume 2000s?",
    "Q5: When a timezone offset causes the UTC date to differ from the local date, which date should be returned?"
  ]

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ length(refined-edge-cases) вүҘ length(gaps) вҶ’ вң“ (7 вүҘ 7)
--   вҠЁ each gap has at least one corresponding test case вҶ’ вң“
--   вҠЁ spec-clarifications addresses each ambiguity вҶ’ вң“ (5 questions for 5 ambiguities)

