  yield complete-suite[], coverage-report, spec-questions[]

  вҲҙ Assemble the final test suite...

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Organize all 22 tests by category, deduplicate, annotate with verdicts.

  yield complete-suite вүЎ [
    -- ISO FORMAT (3 tests, all вң“)
    { input: "2024-03-15", expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: вң“ },
    { input: "2024-03-15T10:30:00Z", expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: вң“ },
    { input: "2024-03-15T23:30:00+05:30", expected: "?", verdict: "? вҖ” timezone ambiguity" },

    -- US FORMAT (2 tests, all вң“)
    { input: "03/15/2024", expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: вң“ },
    { input: "March 15 2024", expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: вң“ },

    -- EUROPEAN FORMAT (2 tests, 1 вң“ + 1 implicit)
    { input: "15.03.2024", expected: Date(2024, 3, 15), verdict: вң“ },
    { input: "13/01/2024", expected: Date(2024, 1, 13), verdict: "вң“ вҖ” implicit disambiguation (month > 12)" },

    -- NATURAL LANGUAGE (3 tests, 1 вң“ + 2 ?)
    { input: "yesterday", expected: "Date(today - 1)", verdict: "вң“ вҖ” but non-deterministic" },
    { input: "next Tuesday", expected: "depends on today", verdict: "? вҖ” anchor ambiguity" },
    { input: "last Wednesday", expected: "depends on today", verdict: "? вҖ” anchor ambiguity" },

    -- AMBIGUOUS FORMAT (2 tests, all ?)
    { input: "01/02/2024", expected: "US: Jan 2 or EU: Feb 1", verdict: "? вҖ” format ambiguity" },
    { input: "03/15/24", expected: "2024 or 1924", verdict: "? вҖ” century pivot" },

    -- BOUNDARY (6 tests, all вң“)
    { input: "2024-02-29", expected: Date(2024, 2, 29), verdict: "вң“ вҖ” leap year valid" },
    { input: "2023-02-29", expected: ValueError, verdict: "вң“ вҖ” leap year invalid" },
    { input: "2000-02-29", expected: Date(2000, 2, 29), verdict: "вң“ вҖ” century leap" },
    { input: "1900-02-29", expected: ValueError, verdict: "вң“ вҖ” century non-leap" },
    { input: "2024-04-31", expected: ValueError, verdict: "вң“ вҖ” day overflow" },
    { input: "2024-00-15", expected: ValueError, verdict: "вң“ вҖ” month zero" },

    -- PARTIAL DATES (1 test, ?)
    { input: "March 2024", expected: "ValueError or Date(2024,3,1)", verdict: "? вҖ” completeness ambiguity" },

    -- ERROR CASES (3 tests, all вң“)
    { input: "not-a-date", expected: ValueError, verdict: вң“ },
    { input: "", expected: ValueError, verdict: вң“ },
    { input: "   ", expected: ValueError, verdict: вң“ }
  ]

  yield coverage-report вүЎ "22 tests across 7 categories. Coverage score: 8/10. 16 tests pass definitively (вң“). 6 tests are ambiguous (?) due to spec gaps, not implementation issues. The test suite discovered 5 spec ambiguities that must be resolved before the function can be fully specified. Key insight: date parsing is dominated by AMBIGUITY, not by bugs. The hardest edge cases aren't about getting the right answer вҖ” they're about defining what 'right' means."

  yield spec-questions вүЎ [
    "Q1: Format disambiguation вҖ” when input matches both US and European formats, which takes precedence? (e.g., '01/02/2024')",
    "Q2: Partial dates вҖ” should 'March 2024' raise ValueError or default missing fields? (dayвҶ’1, monthвҶ’1, yearвҶ’current)",
    "Q3: Relative date anchor вҖ” what reference point for 'next Tuesday'? System clock? Optional parameter?",
    "Q4: Two-digit year pivot вҖ” what century cutoff? POSIX 68/69? Always 2000s?",
    "Q5: Timezone date вҖ” when timezone offset shifts the calendar date, return local or UTC date?"
  ]

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ complete-suite covers initial tests + all edge tests вҶ’ вң“ (22 tests)
--   вҠЁ coverage-report references the coverage-score вҶ’ вң“ ("Coverage score: 8/10")
--   вҠЁ if spec-questions is non-empty then at least one ambiguity was found вҶ’ вң“ (5 questions, 6 ambiguities)
--   вҠЁ complete-suite is organized by category вҶ’ вң“ (7 categories)

-- COMPLETE: 25 eval-one frames (0-24). Function-spec вҶ’ initial tests вҶ’ run вҶ’
-- discover edges вҶ’ spawn вҶ’ edge tests вҶ’ assess вҶ’ refine вҶ’ (вҠўвҲҳ loop) вҶ’ final suite.
-- The program built a 22-test suite from scratch, discovering 5 spec ambiguities
-- and generating 2 iterations of increasingly targeted edge cases.

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- OBSERVATIONS
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў= obs-tests-find-specs
  given В§04-self-building-test-suite
  yield observations

  вҠў= observations вҶҗ "TESTS DISCOVER SPEC BUGS, NOT JUST CODE BUGS: 16 of 22 tests passed. The 6 ambiguous results aren't implementation failures вҖ” they're places where the specification is UNDERSPECIFIED. The test suite evolved from 'does it work?' to 'what does correct mean?' This is the deeper insight: self-building test suites converge on the spec boundary, the place where no amount of testing can substitute for a human decision about intended behavior."

вҠў= obs-recursive-edge-discovery
  given В§04-self-building-test-suite
  yield observations

  вҠў= observations вҶҗ "EDGES DISCOVER DEEPER EDGES: edge-test-1 (ambiguous format 01/02/2024) spawned deeper-edges [13/01/2024, 01/13/2024]. edge-test-2 (leap year 2024) spawned [2000-02-29, 1900-02-29]. Each edge test found 0-3 new edges. The test suite is recursively self-expanding вҖ” like a fractal, each examined boundary reveals finer boundaries beneath it. The вҠўвҠў spawner makes this structural: new cells JOIN THE GRAPH. The frontier grows monotonically. A flat test framework can't do this because tests don't generate tests."

вҠў= obs-evolution-loop-convergence
  given В§04-self-building-test-suite
  yield observations

  вҠў= observations вҶҗ "THE вҠўвҲҳ LOOP CONVERGED IN 2 ITERATIONS: iteration 1 scored 5/10 (only happy paths + first-order edges). Iteration 2 scored 8/10 (boundary cases filled in). The loop STOPPED not because all edges were found, but because the remaining gaps were AMBIGUITIES, not testable edges. This is correct convergence: the loop detects when more tests won't help. Coverage plateaus when the problem shifts from 'test more' to 'spec more'. The coverage oracle correctly distinguished test gaps from spec gaps."

вҠў= obs-spawner-as-test-factory
  given В§04-self-building-test-suite
  yield observations

  вҠў= observations вҶҗ "вҠўвҠў IS A TEST FACTORY: spawn-edge-tests created 8 cells in iteration 1 and 7 in iteration 2. Each spawned cell is a FIRST-CLASS entity in the cell graph вҖ” it has its own givens, yields, oracles, and deeper-edge outputs. This is fundamentally different from a test runner that iterates over a list. Each test cell can REASON about its result and generate MORE tests. The spawner pattern turns test generation into a graph growth problem, where the frontier expands until convergence."

вҠў= obs-ambiguity-as-signal
  given В§04-self-building-test-suite
  yield observations

  вҠў= observations вҶҗ "AMBIGUITY IS THE MOST VALUABLE TEST RESULT: 6 out of 22 tests returned 'ambiguous' verdict. In a traditional test framework, you'd either pick an answer (masking the problem) or skip the test (ignoring it). Cell's three-valued verdict {pass, fail, ambiguous} makes spec gaps VISIBLE. The ambiguous verdict is not a test failure вҖ” it's a DISCOVERY. The spec-questions output is the real deliverable: 5 questions that the function author must answer before the function can be correctly implemented. The test suite built itself into a spec review tool."

вҠў= obs-date-parsing-microcosm
  given В§04-self-building-test-suite
  yield observations

  вҠў= observations вҶҗ "DATE PARSING IS A PERFECT CELL PROBLEM: it looks simple (parse a string), but the input space is a combinatorial minefield. Format ambiguity, locale dependence, calendar math, timezone shifts, partial inputs, relative references вҖ” each category spawns exponentially many edge cases. A static test suite can't explore this space. But Cell's вҠўвҠў spawner + вҠўвҲҳ loop + edge discovery creates an ADAPTIVE EXPLORER that grows its own frontier. The function under test is trivial. The test-generation problem is where the real complexity lives. Cell addresses the META-problem."
